text: Historic counties may refer to: *Historic counties of England, subdivisions of England established for administration by the Normans *Historic counties of Ireland, areas in Ireland separate from the county corporates that existed in some of the larger towns and cities *Historic counties of Scotland, the principal local government divisions of Scotland until 1975 *Historic counties of Wales, ancient sub-divisions of Wales *Counties of Trinidad and Tobago *Counties of Moldova *Former counties of Romania
title: Historic counties
